<Layouts.app flash={@flash}>
  <div class="lg:grid lg:grid-cols-12 mt-5 max-w-5xl mx-auto">
    <.custom_nav active="chelekom-docs-accordion" />
    <div class="lg:col-span-10">
      <.custom_info
        title="Accordion"
        tags={["Component", "Stateless", "JS"]}
        description="Fully featured accordion component for Phoenix LiveView, offering collapsible sections with both custom components and native HTML tags for optimal performance and browser compatibility."
        mix="mix mishka.ui.gen.component accordion"
        github="https://github.com/mishka-group/mishka_chelekom/blob/master/priv/components/accordion.eex"
      />
      <.custom_tab id="chelekom-accordion-tab">
        <:documentation_panel>
          <.heading2 class="mb-5" id="overview">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/accordion/#overview"}>
              Overview of the Phoenix and LiveView Accordion Component
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The
            <strong>
              Mishka Chelekom Accordion
            </strong>
            module offers a wide variety of styles and colors for <strong>Phoenix</strong>, this module allows you to add different variants and colors for a personalized appearance. With options to include icons and media, the accordion is ideal for managing and showcasing data efficiently. Its ability to divide content into collapsible sections provides a clean and functional way to present large volumes of information.
          </.cp>

          <.custom_code_wrapper
            elements_class="grid md:grid-cols-2 mt-10 gap-5 text-sm"
            class="mt-10"
          >
            <.accordion id="chelekom-accordion-4r324" chevron_class="size-4">
              <:item
                id="faq1"
                title="What makes Mishka Chelekom different?"
                icon="hero-question-mark-circle"
                icon_class="size-[17px] text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-200"
                icon_wrapper_class="size-8 flex justify-center items-center shrink-0 rounded-full border border-[#E5E7EB] dark:border-slate-100"
              >
                Mishka Chelekom focuses on developer experience and performance. Built with Phoenix Liveview, it offersvariaty of components, and provides comprehensive documentation with regular updates.
              </:item>

              <:item
                id="faq2"
                title="How can I customize the components?"
                icon="hero-cube"
                icon_class="size-[17px] text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-200"
                icon_wrapper_class="size-8 flex justify-center items-center shrink-0 rounded-full border border-[#E5E7EB] dark:border-slate-100"
              >
                By using various props and different range of values, or class props for component-specific changes. We support Tailwind, and dark mode out of the box.
              </:item>
              <:item
                id="faq3"
                title="How to use Mishka Chelekom?"
                icon="hero-command-line"
                icon_class="size-[17px] text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-200"
                icon_wrapper_class="size-8 flex justify-center items-center shrink-0 rounded-full border border-[#E5E7EB] dark:border-slate-100"
              >
                You can see
                <.link navigate={~p"/chelekom/docs"} title="Mishka Chelekom installation">
                  Getting Started
                </.link>
                page to learn how to integrate Mishka Chelekom into your projects and explore its full capabilities.
              </:item>
            </.accordion>

            <.accordion
              id="chelekom-accordion-example-4242"
              chevron_icon="hero-plus"
              rounded="medium"
              chevron_class="size-4 text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-100"
            >
              <:item
                id="anim1"
                title="Is it animated?"
                description="Mishka chelekon animated accordion"
                icon_class="size-[17px] text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-100"
              >
                Yes, Mishka Chelekom comes with built-in animations for a smoother user experience. These animations are carefully designed to enhance interactions while maintaining performance. The animations include smooth transitions for expanding and collapsing sections, making the interface feel more responsive and polished.
              </:item>

              <:item
                id="anim2"
                title="Is is styled?"
                description="How Mishka chelekom offers different styles?"
                icon_class="size-[17px] text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-100"
              >
                Yes, Mishka Chelekom comes with a variety of built-in styles and theming options. You can customize colors, borders, padding, and other visual elements through props. The styling system is built on Tailwind CSS, making it highly flexible and easy to extend with your own custom styles. Dark mode is also supported out of the box.
              </:item>

              <:item
                id="anim3"
                title="Is is accessible?"
                icon_class="size-[17px] text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-100"
              >
                Yes, Mishka Chelekom is fully accessible. We follow WAI-ARIA standards by implementing proper ARIA attributes, keyboard navigation, and comprehensive screen reader support. We regularly test for compatibility with popular screen readers including NVDA, VoiceOver, and JAWS to ensure a seamless experience for all users.
              </:item>
            </.accordion>

            <.accordion
              id="chelekom-accordion-example-88547"
              chevron_class="size-4 text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-100"
              variant="base_separated"
              rounded="small"
            >
              <:item
                id="sep1"
                title="Is it animated?"
                icon="hero-globe-asia-australia"
                icon_class="size-[0.91rem] text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-100"
              >
                Yes, Mishka Chelekom comes with built-in animations for a smoother user experience. These animations are carefully designed to enhance interactions while maintaining performance. The animations include smooth transitions for expanding and collapsing sections, making the interface feel more responsive and polished.
              </:item>

              <:item
                id="sep2"
                title="Is is styled?"
                icon="hero-inbox-stack"
                icon_class="size-[0.91rem] text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-100"
              >
                Yes, Mishka Chelekom comes with a variety of built-in styles and theming options. You can customize colors, borders, padding, and other visual elements through props. The styling system is built on Tailwind CSS, making it highly flexible and easy to extend with your own custom styles. Dark mode is also supported out of the box.
              </:item>

              <:item
                id="sep3"
                title="Is is accessible?"
                icon="hero-light-bulb"
                icon_class="size-[0.91rem] text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-100"
              >
                Yes, Mishka Chelekom is fully accessible. We follow WAI-ARIA standards by implementing proper ARIA attributes, keyboard navigation, and comprehensive screen reader support. We regularly test for compatibility with popular screen readers including NVDA, VoiceOver, and JAWS to ensure a seamless experience for all users.
              </:item>
            </.accordion>

            <.accordion
              id="chelekom-accordion-423424ewr"
              chevron_class="size-4"
              rounded="large"
              variant="base_separated"
            >
              <:item
                id="nested1"
                title="What makes Mishka Chelekom different?"
                icon="hero-question-mark-circle"
                icon_class="size-[17px] text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-200"
                icon_wrapper_class="size-8 flex justify-center items-center shrink-0 rounded-full border border-[#E5E7EB] dark:border-slate-100"
              >
                Mishka Chelekom focuses on developer experience and performance. Built with Phoenix Liveview, it offersvariaty of components, and provides comprehensive documentation with regular updates.
              </:item>

              <:item
                id="nested2"
                title="How can I customize the components?"
                icon="hero-cube"
                icon_class="size-[17px] text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-200"
                icon_wrapper_class="size-8 flex justify-center items-center shrink-0 rounded-full border border-[#E5E7EB] dark:border-slate-100"
              >
                <.accordion
                  id="chelekom-accordion-789987"
                  variant="transparent"
                  chevron_class="size-4"
                  chevron_icon="hero-plus"
                >
                  <:item
                    id="inner1"
                    title="Can I implement my own styles?"
                    icon="hero-document-magnifying-glass"
                    icon_class="size-[17px] text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-200"
                  >
                    Yes, Mishka Chelekom is highly customizable! You can implement your own styles using custom CSS classes through the class prop, or by overriding our default Tailwind styles. The component is built with flexibility in mind, making it easy to adapt to your specific design needs.
                  </:item>
                  <:item
                    id="inner2"
                    title="IS it hard to modify styles?"
                    icon="hero-globe-alt"
                    icon_class="size-[17px] text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-200"
                  >
                    No, modifying styles is straightforward! You can easily customize the appearance using Tailwind CSS classes or your own custom styles through the class prop. The component's modular design makes it simple to adapt to your specific styling requirements.
                  </:item>
                </.accordion>
              </:item>
              <:item
                id="nested3"
                title="How to use Mishka Chelekom?"
                icon="hero-command-line"
                icon_class="size-[17px] text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-200"
                icon_wrapper_class="size-8 flex justify-center items-center shrink-0 rounded-full border border-[#E5E7EB] dark:border-slate-100"
              >
                You can see
                <.link navigate={~p"/chelekom/docs"} title="Mishka Chelekom installation">
                  Getting Started
                </.link>
                page to learn how to integrate Mishka Chelekom into your projects and explore its full capabilities.
              </:item>
            </.accordion>
          </.custom_code_wrapper>

          <.cp margin="mt-5">
            The Mishka Chelekom <strong>Accordion component</strong>
            also seamlessly integrates with <strong>Phoenix LiveView</strong>
            applications, offering enhanced interactivity. With this
            <.link
              title="Phoenix LiveView component"
              class="transition-colors hover:text-[#448D96]"
              navigate={~p"/chelekom"}
            >
              Phoenix LiveView component
            </.link>
            users can show or hide content effortlessly, while the module’s flexibility with colors and styles ensures that it fits within any design. Whether you’re adding icons, media, or simply dividing complex data into more manageable sections, the accordion component is a versatile solution for improving both functionality and user experience.
          </.cp>

          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="how-to-use-accordion">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/accordion/#how-to-use-accordion"}>
              How to use Phoenix and LiveView accordion component
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The <.link navigate={~p"/chelekom/docs/accordion"}>Mishka Chelekom Accordion</.link>
            module includes a required
            <.custom_inline_code>:item</.custom_inline_code>
            slot, which defines each individual accordion entry. This slot gives you control over elements like the title, description, icons, and more, allowing for easy customization of your accordion items to suit your design and content needs.

            Each item has several attributes:
            <ul class="list-disc px-10">
              <li>
                <strong>title</strong>
                (Required): Specifies the title of the accordion item, which is displayed when the accordion is closed.
              </li>

              <li>
                <strong>description</strong>: A brief description that appears under the title, offering additional context.
              </li>

              <li>
                <strong>icon</strong>: Adds an icon next to the title, enhancing visual representation.
              </li>

              <li>
                <strong>image</strong>: Displays an image next to the accordion item for more interactive content.
              </li>

              <li>
                <strong>hover</strong>: Custom class applied when the item is hovered over, allowing dynamic styling.
              </li>

              <li>
                <strong>open</strong>: A boolean that controls whether the accordion item is open
                <.custom_inline_code>true</.custom_inline_code>
                or closed
                <.custom_inline_code>false</.custom_inline_code>
                by default.
              </li>
            </ul>
            You can check other props of this slot in the props tab.
          </.cp>

          <.custom_code_wrapper elements_class="space-y-3 [&>*]:mb-2 text-sm" code={@code_1}>
            <.accordion id="chelekom-accordion-example34234" color="silver" variant="bordered">
              <:item
                id="why1"
                title="Why Mishka Chelekom?"
                image={~p"/images/avatar3.jpg"}
                image_class="rounded-full"
              >
                Mishka Chelekom is an open-source UI kit for Phoenix and Phoenix LiveView, built with <strong>Tailwind CSS</strong>. It offers essential components like drawers, popovers, and accordions to help developers create responsive, interactive user interfaces effortlessly.

                Start building faster with our easy-to-follow guide, and optimize your Phoenix and LiveView projects with flexible, customizable components.
              </:item>

              <:item
                id="why2"
                title="Is it open-source?"
                image={~p"/images/avatar4.jpg"}
                image_class="rounded-full"
                open={true}
              >
                Mishka Chelekom is a powerful, open-source component library crafted for Phoenix and Phoenix LiveView. Developed using Tailwind CSS, it provides a wide range of UI components, including drawers, popovers, and accordions, to help streamline the creation of responsive, dynamic web applications.

                Boost your development process with our comprehensive guide and start building modern, interactive user interfaces for your Phoenix and LiveView projects effortlessly.
              </:item>
            </.accordion>

            <.accordion
              id="chelekom-accordion-example-one"
              variant="bordered_separated"
              color="info"
              space="large"
            >
              <:item
                id="icon1"
                title="Icon prop Item one"
                description="This accordion accepts icon in summary"
                icon="hero-chat-bubble-left-right-solid"
                icon_class="size-5"
              >
                Select any icon from the Hero Icons website and add its name to the icon prop. The size of the icon can be adjusted using the icon_class prop in each
                slot.
              </:item>

              <:item
                id="icon2"
                title="Icon prop Item two"
                description="This accordion accepts icon in summary"
                icon="hero-chat-bubble-oval-left-ellipsis-solid"
              >
                Select any icon from the Hero Icons website and add its name to the icon prop. The size of the icon can be adjusted using the icon_class prop in each
                slot.
              </:item>
            </.accordion>
          </.custom_code_wrapper>

          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="base-variant">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/accordion/#base-variant"}>
              Base & Base separated Variant
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.custom_code_wrapper elements_class="[&>*]:mb-2 text-sm" code={@code_18}>
            <.accordion id="base-example-120" variant="base">
              <:item id="base1" title="Default variant item one">
                Item one content
              </:item>

              <:item id="base2" title="Default variant item two">
                Item two content
              </:item>
            </.accordion>

            <.accordion id="base-example-110" variant="base_separated" space="small">
              <:item id="basesep1" title="Default variant item one">
                Item one content
              </:item>

              <:item id="basesep2" title="Default variant item two">
                Item two content
              </:item>
            </.accordion>
          </.custom_code_wrapper>

          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="accordion-default-variant">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/accordion/#accordion-default-variant"}>
              Default Variant
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The default variant includes basic styles with a background and borders, providing a clean and simple appearance. You can customize it with different color options, including <.custom_inline_code>natural</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>primary</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>secondary</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>success</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>warning</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>danger</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>info</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>silver</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>misc</.custom_inline_code>, and
            <.custom_inline_code>dawn</.custom_inline_code>
            to match your design needs.
          </.cp>

          <.custom_code_wrapper elements_class="[&>*]:mb-2 text-sm" code={@code_2}>
            <.accordion id="chelekom-accordion-example-323" variant="default" color="primary">
              <:item id="def1" title="Default variant item one">
                Item one content
              </:item>

              <:item id="def2" title="Default variant item two">
                Item two content
              </:item>
            </.accordion>
          </.custom_code_wrapper>

          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="accordion-outline-variant">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/accordion/#accordion-outline-variant"}>
              outline Variant
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The outline variant applies borders only with no background color, giving the component a clean and minimal look. You can customize the border colors with options like <.custom_inline_code>primary</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>secondary</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>natural</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>success</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>warning</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>danger</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>info</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>silver</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>misc</.custom_inline_code>, and <.custom_inline_code>dawn</.custom_inline_code>.
          </.cp>

          <.custom_code_wrapper elements_class="[&>*]:mb-2 text-sm" code={@code_3}>
            <.accordion id="chelekom-accordion-example-three" variant="outline" color="secondary">
              <:item id="out1" title="outline variant item one">
                outline variant item one content
              </:item>

              <:item id="out2" title="outline variant item two">
                outline variant item two content
